{
  "stem": "20021.3",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But if you would go in public places, the German radio would blast the news over the radio publicly for the population to listen.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "You learned to listen to their news and day from day to somehow figure out where they are lying, because everything was lies.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But you figured it out in sort of like a, you know, you developed a method where you could guess due to the fact that they were saying one day this and the other day that, gee, there must be some big trouble now at, you now, Stalingrad and all that.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And together with that newspaper, people were informed during the war-- not up to date, but they were informed.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So But not in that time-- when I left in 1942, Hitler looked very victorious, very victorious.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "This was just a year after France and Hitler marched into Paris.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And the British were-- were running away, you know, in-- in I forgot the name of the town, [INAUDIBLE] or whatever the name was, where the whole British fleet was running for their life.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "He was so powerful.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And then in 1941, when he attacked Russia, Russia crumbled.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Russia was supposed to be a power, you know, and they-- they crumbled.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "So-- so that, in 1942, although I didn't doubt that he would lose the war because if you doubted that he'd lose the war, you might as well stop living, you know.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "You had to believe.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "But there were no actual signs of the fact of his impending defeat.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "A year later, it became very clear after Stalingrad that it will be different.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Stalingrad was then turn.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Went to Lwow June 1942.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
